headlines.description: — The Denver Nuggets have been so dominant this season that they've clinched the Northwest Division with a few weeks left in the regular season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nuggets top Pistons to end skid, clinch Northwest Division

headlines.description: — For the first time in 17 years, Sacramento has a winning team again.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kings beat Nets, clinch first winning season since 2005-06

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Toronto Raptors

headlines.description: — Pascal Siakam had 25 points and 14 rebounds to help the Toronto Raptors beat the Oklahoma City Thunder 128-111 on Thursday night, extending their season-high home winning streak to six.
headlines.shortLinkText: Raptors win sixth straight at home, beat Thunder 128-111

headlines.description: — Andrew Nembhard scored 24 points and Aaron Nesmith hit six 3-pointers and finished with 22 points as the Indiana Pacers rallied late and beat the Central Division- and Eastern Conference-leading Milwaukee Bucks 139-123 Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pacers rally late, beat Eastern Conference-leading Bucks

headlines.description: — Josh Okogie made a go-ahead 3-pointer midway through the fourth quarter and blocked Paolo Banchero's 3 in the final seconds as the Phoenix Suns held off the Orlando Magic 116-113 on Thursday night to snap a three-game losing streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Suns hold off Magic 116-113, snap 3-game losing streak
